Stapylton County was named in honour of the geologist, Granville William Chetwynd Stapylton (1800-1902).
Stapylton County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It is located to the south of the Barwon River and includes part of the Newell Highway .
